{"id":14881812,"mediaExerciseId":"c36f17cf-fa70-4fb8-b003-85ea9ecc10ad","exerciseName":"2","chapterName":"23","chapterTitle":"Enterprise Risk Management","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":"23.2","sectionTitle":"Managing Financial Risk","pageNumber":769,"solutions":[{"id":5990253,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will talk about what a risk profile is and how companies can counteract risks through the process of hedging. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**2a.** A risk profile is a graph/plot that visualizes a company's tolerance to risk. It describes the relation between the price change of their goods and their company's stock valuation. This allows both the company and its investors to understand the risk exposure of the company given the different changes in the price as well as the supply in the market. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":181,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/4e8cf7032d41d33cc61e93c8b1f4ccc2/8ce778da429952750fa4fca62288d7d5/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/4e8cf7032d41d33cc61e93c8b1f4ccc2/8ce778da429952750fa4fca62288d7d5/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"**2b.** Hedging refers to the practice of using different financial strategies, especially in trading, to offset the possible losses that can be brought by sudden changes in the price. \n\nThis can help the firm as it protects them from the possible volatility of the market by engaging in short trades so that when the value does decrease, they can still get gains from their market. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":218,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/07/4e8cf7032